        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 13 at 5:43AM MDT by NWS Glasgow MT</headline>
        <description>At 542 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles west of Bredette, or 19 miles south of Scobey, moving east at
25 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bredette.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
